article.headline: Grambling State 63, Alabama A&M 52
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- With 17 points and 13 rebounds, Anthony Williams led Grambling State to a 63-52 win over Alabama A&M Tuesday night. The Tigers (3-5, 1-0 SWAC) scored their first point with 18:41 left in the first half and kept their lead for the rest of the game. Grambling also outrebounded the Bulldogs (5-7, 0-1 SWAC) by 50-22. Kendric Baker added 13 points for the Tigers, and Andrew Prestley chipped in with 12 points and 10 rebounds. Alabama A&M had two players who scored in the double digits -- Jonathan Belt with 12 points and Evan Hilton with 11.
